Hi Peter,

Long-time JS Weekly reader. Sharing something you might find fits the
"unusual and small" corner of the newsletter.

I recently released three MIT-licensed browser libraries that compose
but each solves its own problem:

- @0xsarwagya/ghost — persistent identity via non-extractable Ed25519
  CryptoKey in IndexedDB. No accounts, no OIDC. Ed25519 finally
  cross-browser as of Safari 17.4.
  https://oss.sarwagya.wtf/ghost/docs

- @0xsarwagya/handoff — JSON state transfer up to ~8 KiB via URL
  fragment or QR (deflate-raw + base64url + a qrFriendly boolean).
  https://oss.sarwagya.wtf/handoff/docs

- @0xsarwagya/durable-local — one named JSON value in IndexedDB with
  atomic RMW, migrations, and honest durability categorization
  (session/ephemeral/best-effort/persistent/ios-capped — because
  navigator.storage.persisted() lies on Safari desktop tabs).
  https://oss.sarwagya.wtf/durable-local/docs

